# SYSTEM SPECIFICATION DOCUMENT (SPECS)

## Livelihood Security Platform — Desktop Admin Application (POC)

---

## 1. Document Purpose

This document specifies the **functional, behavioral, architectural, and operational specifications** for the **Desktop Admin Application (Electron)** used to run a livelihood income-stabilization pilot.

This is the **highest-authority implementation document** for the POC.

If something is not in this document, it is **not required**.

---

## 2. System Scope

### In Scope

* Desktop Admin App (Electron)
* Backend APIs
* Income Guarantee logic
* Payment execution
* Immutable work ledger
* Offline-tolerant ops

### Out of Scope

* Worker-facing apps
* UI branding or aesthetics
* Insurance / credit systems
* Production scalability
* Mobile or web clients

---

## 3. Operating Reality (Hard Constraints)

### User Reality

* Power users only
* Long sessions (multi-hour)
* High data density
* Low tolerance for ambiguity
* Explicit control preferred over automation

### System Reality

* Unreliable network
* Manual overrides required
* Auditability mandatory
* Partial automation acceptable

---

## 4. Global Design Rules (Enforced)

1. Predictability > beauty
2. Explicit actions only
3. No hidden state
4. One screen = one responsibility
5. Append-only financial records
6. Manual override always possible
7. Fail visibly, never silently

---

## 5. Layout & Interaction Specifications

### Layout

| Rule      | Spec             |
| --------- | ---------------- |
| Grid      | 12-column        |
| Base unit | 8px              |
| Max width | 1600px           |
| Sidebar   | Fixed, 240–280px |
| Top bar   | Sticky           |

### Interaction

* Keyboard usable for all primary actions
* Explicit save / submit actions only
* Confirmation required for destructive actions
* No animation conveys meaning

🚫 Never:

* Centered layouts
* Auto-save
* Hidden confirmations
* Playful motion

---

## 6. Navigation & Information Architecture

### Primary Modules (L1)

| Module           | Responsibility               |
| ---------------- | ---------------------------- |
| Dashboard        | System overview (read-only)  |
| Workers          | Worker registry              |
| Jobs             | Work definition & assignment |
| Income Guarantee | Rule configuration           |
| Payments         | Execution & reconciliation   |
| Work History     | Immutable ledger             |
| Reports          | Export & compliance          |
| Settings         | System configuration         |

Navigation depth **must not exceed 2 levels**.

---

## 7. Core Functional Specifications

### 7.1 Worker Management

* Create worker
* Edit worker attributes
* Activate / deactivate worker
* View work summary

**Rules**

* No deletion
* No document dependency
* Deactivated workers retain history

---

### 7.2 Job Management

* Create job with:

  * Skill
  * Rate
  * Date
  * Minimum guarantee
* Assign workers
* Explicitly close job

**Rules**

* Jobs editable until closed
* Closed jobs immutable
* No silent reassignment

---

### 7.3 Income Guarantee Engine

* Define minimum income rules:

  * Daily or weekly
  * Global or job-level
* Calculate earnings vs guarantee
* Compute deterministic top-ups

**Rules**

* Rules apply forward-only
* Calculations logged
* No retroactive changes

---

### 7.4 Payments

* Review payable workers
* Trigger single or batch payouts
* Retry failed payments
* View transaction references

**Rules**

* Payments immutable once triggered
* Manual retry required
* Partial failures surfaced explicitly

---

### 7.5 Work History (Ledger)

* Auto-generated from jobs + payments
* Append-only
* Read-only views

**Rules**

* No edits
* No deletions
* Source of truth for audits

---

### 7.6 Reports

* Daily summary
* Worker earnings
* Top-up usage
* CSV export

**Rules**

* Reports are derived views
* No direct edits

---

## 8. Behavioral Specifications

### Entity Mutability

| Entity         | Editable | Lock Condition |
| -------------- | -------- | -------------- |
| Worker         | Yes      | Never          |
| Job            | Yes      | On close       |
| Guarantee Rule | Yes      | Future only    |
| Payment        | No       | Immediate      |
| Ledger Entry   | No       | Always         |

---

### Action Outcomes

Every state-changing action must return one of:

* `success`
* `partial_success`
* `failed`
* `requires_manual_review`

---

## 9. Offline & Failure Behavior

### Offline Mode

* Read-only UI
* Cached edits allowed (non-financial)
* Payment actions disabled
* Manual sync on reconnect

### Failure Categories

* Validation failure
* Network failure
* Payment provider failure
* Data conflict

Failures must be **visible and actionable**.

---

## 10. Technical Architecture Specification

### Desktop Layer

* Electron
* React (functional components)
* Local SQLite cache
* Keyboard shortcut engine

### Backend Layer

* REST APIs
* Stateless services
* JWT authentication
* Business rule engine
* Audit logger

